  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>The problem was that some people had disappeared from the people-search index. I 
fixed it -- now when you go to <a href="https://openhatch.org/+projects/Evince">https://openhatch.org/+projects/Evince</a> and see '6 
people who can mentor in C', and click the link to 
<a href="https://openhatch.org/people/?q=can_mentor:%22C%22">https://openhatch.org/people/?q=can_mentor:%22C%22</a> , you see six people.

For our own future reference, here's what I did to fix it:

In [21]: for person in Person.objects.all():
    pi  = mysite.profile.search_indexes.PersonIndex(person)
    print '.',
    pi.update_object(person)

I don't really like the Haystack API, but there's a magic incantation for you 
that works.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
